articles.title: About
articles.contents:
This blog documents activity as it happens in the 2021 pilot of Kaneâ€™s Free High School Data Science Bootcamp. The course is adapted from GOV:1005, an introductory data science course which Harvard Preceptor David Kane taught. You can find out more at the bootcamp website.
The course involves live lecture three times a week by Preceptor Kane, working tutorials written by Preceptor Kane and his staff, student final projects, and a thriving Discord, which forms the main subject of this blog.
